# ripplegraph workflow - host agent guide

This document is the protocol contract for any host agent driving this
workflow. Use `ripplegraph-demo` for normal work; use `ripplegraph` only when
you need low-level JSON for debugging. The filesystem state is authoritative.

## Commands

Use these commands from the workflow root:

```sh
ripplegraph-demo status --workflow-root .
ripplegraph-demo start <graph-id> --run <run-id> --workflow-root .
ripplegraph-demo submit '<json>' --workflow-root .
ripplegraph-demo pause "pause current work" --workflow-root .
ripplegraph-demo resume <run-id> --workflow-root .
ripplegraph-demo runs --workflow-root .
```

## Loop

1. Run `ripplegraph-demo status --workflow-root .`.
2. Read the current node purpose, instructions, and required output.
3. Do the work requested by the node.
4. Submit JSON with `ripplegraph-demo submit '<json>' --workflow-root .`.
5. Continue until the run reaches a terminal node.

## Switching work

Only one run is current at a time. To change focus, suspend the current run and
start or resume another run. Do not edit `.ripplegraph/current.json` by hand
unless the CLI cannot recover.

## Files

```sh
workflow.json
.ripplegraph/current.json
.ripplegraph/runs/<run-id>/checkpoint.json
.ripplegraph/runs/<run-id>/transition-log.jsonl
```

If conversation memory conflicts with these files, trust the files.

